        "sanskrit": "गौरीकराम्बुजन्यस्तस्वर्णशैलशरासनम् । इषुहस्तं रथारूढं नरनारीतनुं स्मरेत् ॥",
        "english": "One should meditate on the Lord in the form of Ardhanarishvara (half man, half woman), seated on a chariot, holding an arrow in his hand, and holding a bow (the golden Meru mountain) placed there by the lotus hands of Gauri."
